affic to main roads. Shopping centres to be pedestrian priority with cycling and careful deliveries tolerated. Minor roads to be limited to 20mph.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">2)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">On main roads the provision of segregated cycling facilities as ess</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ential as the provision of footways. (This does not mean cycling on footways). </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">3)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Main junctions should have clear separation of motor vehicles, cycles and pedestrians.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">4)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> As different vehicles cause different degrees of danger a greater responsibility lies wi</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">th the driver of a heavier vehicle. Some form of default liability operates in most European countries. Making cyclists default liable in collision with pedestrians might make this more palatable. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">5)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">HGVs that are allowed into towns need to be designed to be</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> able to operate safely in the presence of pedestrians and cyclists. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">You will have heard these ideas before â€“ please do not allow yourselves to be deflected into a futile blame-game between drivers and cyclists. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">December 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>